title.narrative: 3.2 CHILDREN AND WOMEN AT RISK OF VIOLENCE AND EXPLOITATION HAVE IMPROVED ACCESS

description.narrative: Children and women at risk of violence and exploitation have improved access to an integrated package of quality child protection and gender-based violence prevention and response services., which contributes to Communication And Advocacy, Cross-Sectoral - Human Rights, Cross-Sectoral - Other Programme Areas, Promotion Of Care, Mental Health And Psychosocial Well-Being And Justice, Protection From Violence, Exploitation, Abuse And Neglect. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Improved and equitable prevention of and response to violence, abuse, exploitation and neglect of children.

description.narrative: UNICEF continued to build the capacities of government and NGO partners to deliver quality CP and GBV response and prevention services. MoE, MoH and FPJD adopted and implemented specific SOPs on CP and GBV cases, highlighting the continuous institutionalization of case management within government. Prioritizing strengthening of the social service workforce by MoSD was a key advancement, with mapping planned for 2022.15,131 individuals (5,575 girls, 7,797 boys and 1,759 women)accessed integrated case management services, 66,069 children(36,571 girls, 29,498 boys)participated in structured and sustained CP and PSS programmes. MHPSS programmes in MoE schools reached200,000 students. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:22/12/2021
